        "cooked": "<p><strong>Note</strong>: This library has moved to charmlibs</p>\n<p>The TLS Certificates Interface is a charm relation interface for securely requesting and providing TLS certificates in the charm ecosystem.</p>\n<p>The TLS Certificates Library is a library that automate the management of certificates in charms using the TLS Certificates Interface.</p>\n<p>This documentation is meant for <strong>charm authors</strong>.</p>\n<h2><a name=\"p-27204-in-this-documentation-1\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-27204-in-this-documentation-1\"></a>In this documentation</h2>\n<div class=\"md-table\">\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th></th>\n<th></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Tutorials</strong><br>  Get started - a hands-on introduction for new users<br></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Explanation</strong><br> Concepts - discussion and clarification of key topics <br></td>\n<td><strong>Reference</strong><br> Technical information - specifications, APIs, architecture</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div><h2><a name=\"p-27204-project-and-community-2\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-27204-project-and-community-2\"></a>Project and community</h2>\n<p>The TLS Certificates Library is a member of the Ubuntu family. It\u2019s an open source project that warmly welcomes community projects, contributions, suggestions, fixes and constructive feedback.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://ubuntu.com/community/ethos/code-of-conduct\">Code of conduct</a></li>\n<li>Meet the community and chat with us on <a href=\"https://matrix.to/#/!yAkGlrYcBFYzYRvOlQ:ubuntu.com?via=ubuntu.com&amp;via=matrix.org&amp;via=gnome.org\">Matrix</a></li>\n<li>Contribute and report bugs to the library on <a href=\"https://github.com/canonical/tls-certificates-interface\">GitHub</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h1><a name=\"p-27204-navigation-3\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-27204-navigation-3\"></a>Navigation</h1>\n<div class=\"md-table\">\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Level</th>\n<th>Path</th>\n<th>Navlink</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>tutorials</td>\n<td><a>Tutorials</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-getting-started</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/15537\">Getting Started (v4)</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Explanation</td>\n<td><a>Explanation</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-tls-certificates-interface</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/15539\">TLS Certificates Interface</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-common-name-and-sans-attributes</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/19118\"> Common Name and SANs Attributes</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-certificate-renewal</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/15542\">Automated Certificate Renewal (v4)</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-library-differences-v3-to-v4</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/17225\">TLS Certificates Library v3 vs v4</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-security</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/18245\">Security</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Reference</td>\n<td><a>(For Charm Developers) Reference</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-library-versions</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/15555\">Library Versions</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-private-key-label-change</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/16764\">Change of private key labels in V4.8</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-recommended-config-options</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/15541\">Recommended Configuration Options</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Reference</td>\n<td><a>(For Charm Users)  Reference</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-securing-internal-communication</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/18382\">Securing Internal Communication</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-securing-api-communication</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/18385\">Securing API Communication</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>h-ca-trust-best-practices</td>\n<td><a href=\"/t/18386\">CA Trust Best Practices</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>",
