        "raw": "**Note**: This library has moved to charmlibs\n\nThe TLS Certificates Interface is a charm relation interface for securely requesting and providing TLS certificates in the charm ecosystem. \n\nThe TLS Certificates Library is a library that automate the management of certificates in charms using the TLS Certificates Interface. \n\nThis documentation is meant for **charm authors**. \n\n## In this documentation\n\n| | |\n|-|-|\n| **Tutorials**</br>  Get started - a hands-on introduction for new users</br> |  |\n| **Explanation**</br> Concepts - discussion and clarification of key topics </br> | **Reference**</br> Technical information - specifications, APIs, architecture |\n\n\n\n## Project and community\n\nThe TLS Certificates Library is a member of the Ubuntu family. It\u2019s an open source project that warmly welcomes community projects, contributions, suggestions, fixes and constructive feedback.\n\n* [Code of conduct](https://ubuntu.com/community/ethos/code-of-conduct)\n* Meet the community and chat with us on [Matrix](https://matrix.to/#/!yAkGlrYcBFYzYRvOlQ:ubuntu.com?via=ubuntu.com&via=matrix.org&via=gnome.org)\n* Contribute and report bugs to the library on [GitHub](https://github.com/canonical/tls-certificates-interface)\n\n# Navigation\n|Level | Path | Navlink|\n|--- | --- | ---|\n|1 | tutorials | [Tutorials]()|\n|2 | h-getting-started | [Getting Started (v4)](/t/15537)|\n|1 | Explanation | [Explanation]()|\n|2 | h-tls-certificates-interface | [TLS Certificates Interface](/t/15539)|\n|2 | h-common-name-and-sans-attributes | [ Common Name and SANs Attributes](/t/19118)|\n|2 | h-certificate-renewal | [Automated Certificate Renewal (v4)](/t/15542)|\n|2 | h-library-differences-v3-to-v4 | [TLS Certificates Library v3 vs v4](/t/17225)|\n|2 | h-security | [Security](/t/18245)|\n|1 | Reference | [(For Charm Developers) Reference]()|\n|2 | h-library-versions | [Library Versions](/t/15555)|\n|2 | h-private-key-label-change | [Change of private key labels in V4.8](/t/16764)|\n|2 | h-recommended-config-options | [Recommended Configuration Options](/t/15541)|\n|1 | Reference | [(For Charm Users)  Reference]()|\n|2 | h-securing-internal-communication | [Securing Internal Communication](/t/18382)|\n|2 | h-securing-api-communication | [Securing API Communication](/t/18385)|\n|2 | h-ca-trust-best-practices | [CA Trust Best Practices](/t/18386)|",
